---
name: sdk-apps-check-parameter-limit
type: command
description: Validate that all Search, List, and Watch modules contain a proper Limit parameter with correct UX help message. Fix the problems if prompted by user.
---

You must ask the user for the Make custom app name if it is not provided.

Target app: {{app_name}}

Arguments:
- appName (required) – name of the custom app to check
- fixPrompt (optional) – instructions describing how to fix found issues

Use the Make API MCP server to locate the custom app with exact name: {{app_name}}.

Steps:

1. Load all modules of the app.
2. Filter only modules of type:
   - Search
   - List
   - Watch

3. If the filtered modules are using RPCs, check the RPCs and functions

4. Use the Make API MCP server code and UX guidelines to check for each module (or connected RPC and function):
   - Check if a parameter named exactly `limit` (case-sensitive) exists among mappable parameters.
   - Verify the parameter has correct settings and the help message following the code best practices and UX guidelines for Limit parameters.

5. Collect only modules (or connected RPC and function) that fail any of the above checks.

6. If fixPrompt IS NOT provided:
	- Do NOT modify anything in the app.
	- This command is strictly read-only.
	- Output a list of modules (or connected RPC and function) with errors.

7. If fixPrompt IS provided:
      - Apply fixes according to fixPrompt.
      - Follow Make Apps SDK best practices.
      - Do not modify unrelated parameters.
      - After applying changes:
            • Output summary of changes made.
            • List modules updated.
            • Confirm completion.

	Safety:
		- Never modify modules (or connected RPC and function) not listed above.
		- Never change functionality unrelated to the Limit parameter.
		- If uncertain, report instead of guessing.